Right Join - 
	 A RIGHT JOIN (or RIGHT OUTER JOIN) in SQL is used to combine rows from two tables-
	 Returns all rows from the right table, and Matching rows from the left table.
	 If there is no match in the left table, it returns NULL for left table columns.
	 Right table = the table written after RIGHT JOIN.
	 
	Employee - emp_id, emp_name, dept_id
	Department - dept_id, dept_name
	
	SELECT e.emp_id, e.emp_name, d.dept_name
	FROM employee e
	RIGHT JOIN department d
	ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;
	 